name: annual-monitoring-report-for-dorris-reservoir-modoc-national-wildlife-refuge-water-year-19-fe3b7
notes: This is an annual water use report based on the Monitoring Plan for Dorris Reservoir. Table 1 provides monthly summaries of the information for the  1997 water year. Appendix A explains the notation and calculations used. Data includes volume and time of releases and bypass from Dorris Reservoir, the elevation of water levels, the volume of water held in Dorris Reservoir and evaporation from Dorris Reservoir. Calculated are the volume of water stored in Dorris Reservoir, the volume of water directly diverted through Dorris Reservoir, and the contributions to storage and direct diversion from (1) Parker Creek, (2) Pine Creek and (3) Stockdill Slough.  Table I provides monthly summaries of the information requested in Term 5 of the Order for the 1996 water year. Appendix A explains the notation and calculations used. Appendix B provides the updated capacity table and capacity curve for Dorris Reservoir. Appendix C is the flood flow  documentation.
